whereas Virtue, if a pauper, is stopped at all frontiers. So Jonah’s Captain 
prepares to test the length of Jonah’s purse, ere he judge him openly. He 
charges him thrice the usual sum; and it’s assented to. Then the Captain 
knows that Jonah is a fugitive; but at the same time resolves to help a flight 
that paves its rear with gold. Yet when Jonah fairly takes out his purse, 
